The new RES Law also provides other incentives 
such as:
 Establishment of a national RES target in the total energy final consumption;
 Obligatory connection to the transmission or distribution networks;
 Payment only of the direct costs of connection to the electricity transmission or distribution 
networks;
 Long-term (15 years) power purchase agreements for the electricity produced from Priority 
RES power plants up to 15 MW installed capacity will remain the same.

The cascade comprises seven HPPs: Sevan (34 MW); Hrazdan (81 MW); 
Argel (224 MW); Arzni (70 MW); Kanaker (102 MW); Yerevan-1 (44 MW); and Yerevan-3 (5 MW), with 
a total installed capacity of 560 MW and designed to produce up to 2.32 billion kWh annually.

